HEADWORD: Haaf
<hw>Haaf</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of Scand. origin;
cf. Icel. & Sw. <ets>haf</ets> the sea, Dan. <ets>hav</ets>, perh. akin
to E. <ets>haven</ets>.]</ety> <def>The deep-sea fishing for cod, ling,
and tusk, off the Shetland Isles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

